All Implemented Interfaces:
com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core.CartographicSupport, com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core.IPrintable, com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core.symbols.ILineSymbol, com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core.symbols.ISymbol, com.iver.utiles.IPersistence
public class PictureLineSymbol
extends com.iver.cit.gvsig.fmap.core.symbols.AbstractLineSymbol

PictureLineSymbol allows to use any symbol defined as an image (by an image file) supported by gvSIG.This symbol will be used as an initial object.The line will be painted as a succession of puntual symbols through the path defined by it(the line).

Author:
jaume dominguez faus - jaume.dominguez@iver.es
